voices.mp3Text: Let them try and stop me.
My horn is sharp, my pike is sharper still.
Keep your eye on my horn!
By the gleam of my horn!
Under my hoof you will find your fate.
Let them try and stop me.
My horn is sharp, my pike is sharper still.
Keep your eye on my horn!
Since I vowed to reclaim our homeland, I have never made a stauncher oath. But I swear, this one is in the bag.
It's as plain as the horn on my head. This one is in the bag.
Horn calls to horn and it begins!
Ha ha, the thunder of hooves!
By the gleam of my horn!
Under my hoof you will find your fate.
Ha ha, no match for me!
Yes, the thunder you hear is my hooves.
You shall perish upon my horn.
Ah, my strength knows no bounds.
Who else has such a horn.
The power warms me from within.
Ah ha ha ha ha ha ha ha!
Ah ha ha ha ha ha ha!
Ha ha ha ha! What did you expect?
I think you got the point.
Accustom yourself to loss. It suits you.
Ah, trampled! Ha ha ha ha!
The horn that gored you was precious beyond all measure.
I faced down a volcano. What made you think you stood a chance?
Answer me, eh. Was it worth your life to try for my horn?
You must have mistaken my purpose…to flatten you!
Ha ha! Tip of the horn to you!
Yeah, ha ha ha ha ha!
Ah, ha ha ha ha ha!
Eh ha ha ha ha ha ha ha!
Ah ha ha ha ha ha.
Ha ha ha ha ha ha ha ha!
Ah ha ha ha ha ha.
Ah ha ha ha ha ha.
What do you mean, I'm not your type?
I do have a gentler side, Enchantress.
Was it something I said, Enchantress?
Is it too late to court?
Hm, that was one fiery wench.
Too chilly for my tastes, maiden.
I prefer the talkative types, Ranger.
Spirit, you could use more meat on your bones.
I am sorry I hurt you, creature. But not your rider.
The true rogue knight would not so easily fall.
Only I shall shake the earth from now on.
You call yourself a master of beasts? I think not.
You're no match for me, Tidehunter!
You're no match for me, fishfingers!
You're no match for me, fishstick!
You planted your roots in the wrong path.
Too many legs make for a messy gait.
I'll not be cowed by any fish.
I have tartar sauce for people like you.
Ah, first blood, and so much more shall soon be spilled!
Let us trample them together, Spirit Breaker!
I could show you the meaning of pain, oh Queen.
Why are all the good ones dead, Death Prophet?
Stick with me, Leshrac, and we'll go far.
I'll repay you when I can.
Beg my pardon and my pike!
Ah ha ha ha ha ha ha!
Ah, I horned in on you.
Ah ha ha ha ha hah!
Ah ha ha ha ha ha ha!
Twas costly but not compared to the value of my horn.
Compared to my horn, all precious items are cheap.
Yes, this will do just fine.
Scepter is no horn, but I prize it nonetheless.
Sharp indeed, even compared to my horn.
Pick on someone your own size.
Have I finally met my match?
I survived an eruption but died to this?
My lost kin wait for me.
You'll die on this horn next time.
Touch my horn and be cursed.
They can hurt my body but not my pride.
I am magnanimous to a point.
I won't go so easy on them this time.
I have failed you once but not again.
Give me a moment to polish my horn.
It will take more than death to discourage me.
Set me against the enemy once more.
This shall come in handy later.
Yes, this will do just fine.
A bounty which my matriarch will prize!
One horn will do the damage of two.
I'll hurry my foe to a spiky end!
Three horns on which to hoist them!
Strength renewed and purpose with it.

voices.mp3Text: Whosoever brought the fires of Mt. Joerlak down upon my kin, know this: You are craven. I shall track you down, and once I do, you shall die upon my horn. Slowly.
I have long since lost count of however many fools and weaklings I have slain by pike, by horn, or by hoof. Though let me assure you: The process never ceases to be entertaining.
Behold the horn of Magnus. Aah, does it not dazzle and delight you?
No, I blame no one who covets my horn. But to desire more than sight of it is a guarantee of death.
I tell you what. You touch my horn, I break your face.
Eh ha ha ha ha ha ha ha!
Ah ha ha ha ha ha.
Ha ha ha ha ha ha ha ha!
Ah ha ha ha ha ha.
Ah ha ha ha ha ha.
At last with horn held high, I may rejoin my kin.
A token sure to quicken my people's return!
A bounty which my matriarch will prize!
What is this? A treasure that almost withstands comparison to the horn of Magnus!
